data.description: Designed for easy living, this one-level home combines classic style with storybook charm. The open concept layout optimizes natural light, expands entertainment options, creates a seamless flow between rooms and utilizes the entire space, making the home feel bigger than it is. The living room greets guests with an inviting fireplace and the kitchen has a raised eating bar and built-in pantry with a solar tube providing natural light throughout the day.  The primary suite is away from the other bedrooms and offers both a private ensuite bath with double sinks and a large walk-in closet.  The dining area features a two-tone beadboard accent wall with a picture window and can be easily transformed from informal to formal and accommodate various table sizes for a multitude of guests. The 4th bedroom is in the front of the house and could also make a great office/study. Outside, the trellised patio is encompassed by beautiful climbing shade plants that bloom with purple flowers.  Custom-built wood planters made with commercial grade metal framing have been pre-treated and potting soil packed inside. An inviting flagstone patio, framed by planter beds, offers open seating and a kiva-style stove with space to add a firepit/fire table. The HUGE oversized 2-car garage has custom shelving lining the way and storage areas on both sides provide ample storage space. The RV parking area widens out past the gate for even more room to store smaller toys, trailers, atvs, etc. and the giant storage shed will keep all your implements dry, neat and organized. A rare find…tucked in the trees on a cul-de-sac lot in Comstock Estates.  Close to schools, medical offices, the hospital & the Fruita Rec Center.  Less than a mile to downtown Fruita area shops and restaurants and world-famous hiking & mountain biking trails nearby!
